Abuja – President Muhammadu Buhari and 14 governors arrived Kano on Saturday to grace the wedding of Fatima Ganduje and Idris Ajimobi, both children of the Kano and Oyo states governors,  Abdullahi Ganjude and Abiola Ajimobi, respectively. Apart from Ganjude and Ajimobi, other governors at the event are Akinwumi Ambode (Lagos); Rochas Okorocha (Imo); Yahaya Bello (Kogi); Abdul Aziz Yari (Zamfara); Simon Lalung (Plateau) and Nasir El Rufai (Kaduna). Others are: Rauf Aregbesola (Osun); Mohammed Abubakar (Bauchi); Ibikunle Amosun (Ogun); Badaru Abubakar (Jigawa); Abubakar Bagudu (Kebbi) and Kashim Shettima (Borno). Others prominent political figures, who graced the event, included Bukola Saraki, the President of the Senate, Bola Ahmed Tinubu, the National leader of the All Progressive Congress (APC). There were also a retinue of top government officials, technocrats, captains of industries and diplomats, as well as wife of the Vice President, Oludolapo Osinbajo, who arrived Kano on Friday, accompanied by wives of 15 state governors. The wedding fatiha held at the Kano Central Mosque, adjacent to the Emir of Kano’s palace and lasted for just 15 minutes. The Emir of Kano, Lamido Sanusi ll, officiated the wedding, while the groom’s family was represented by President Buhari, who presented a bride price (Sadaki) of N50,000 to the bride’s family, represented by former Lagos State governor, Tinubu, who received the bride price on behalf of the family. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.